description:
Mr. Ron Carter is one of the most famous bassists in history. But did you know he started out playing cello? In this episode (2 of 4) Mr. Carter talks to fellow Epifani artist KJ (The Oddysy) about how he got started with music back in grade school.

KJ also asks about the electric bass. The answer: Ron can certainly play it, but it's not his main thing. 

Ron Carter says classical music is his balm, his salve. The proof is in his solo recording Ron Carter Meets Bach, a multi-bass homage to the great European composer. All parts played by Mr. Carter himself.

Ron Carter plays Epifani amps exclusively. In this video you see him with his UL 901 bass amp and DIST 1x12 dual-impedance bass speaker cabinet.

Interview by KJ (Kevin Jacoby) of The Oddysy (www.TheOddysy.com)
Audio / Video by Shapeshifter Lab
Editing by Ruddy Alcantara
